    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "1.\n",
        "*   Mean: $E[Y] = E[X] + E[Q] = 0 + 0 = 0$$E[Y] = E[X] + E[Q] = 0 + 0 = 0$.\n",
        "*   Variance: Since $X \\perp Q$$X \\perp Q$, $\\text{Var}(Y) = \\text{Var}(X) + \\text{Var}(Q) = 1 + 4 = 5$$\\text{Var}(Y) = \\text{Var}(X) + \\text{Var}(Q) = 1 + 4 = 5$.\n",
        "\n",
        "*   Covariance: $\\text{Cov}(X, Y) = E[XY] - E[X]E[Y] = E[X(X+Q)] = E[X^2] + E[XQ]$$\\text{Cov}(X, Y) = E[XY] - E[X]E[Y] = E[X(X+Q)] = E[X^2] + E[XQ]$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Since $E[X^2] = \\text{Var}(X) = 1$$E[X^2] = \\text{Var}(X) = 1$ and $E[XQ] = E[X]E[Q] = 0$$E[XQ] = E[X]E[Q] = 0$:\n",
        "$\\text{Cov}(X, Y) = 1$\n",
        "\n",
        "The joint distribution is: $$\\begin{pmatrix} X \\\\ Y \\end{pmatrix} \\sim \\mathscr{N} \\left( \\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\\\ 0 \\end{pmatrix}, \\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 1 \\\\ 1 & 5 \\end{pmatrix} \\right)$$\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "W42vXhH-wqWt"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "2. $X$ is not $\\sigma(Y)$-measurable because there is no deterministic function $g$ such that $X = g(Y)$. For any observed $Y=y$, there are infinitely many pairs $(x, q)$ such that $x+q=y$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xoEgFJcgV1xQ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "3. For bivariate normal variables, the best mean-square estimate is:\n",
        "$$E[X \\mid Y = y] = \\mu_X + \\frac{\\text{Cov}(X,Y)}{\\text{Var}(Y)}(y - \\mu_Y) = 0 + \\frac{1}{5}(y - 0)$$\n",
        "$$\\mathbf{E[X \\mid Y] = 0.2 Y}$$\n",
        "**Interpretation:** Because the noise ($Q$) is 4 times more volatile than the signal ($X$), we only \"trust\" 20% of the power fluctuation as being caused by temperature."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mgn57xWMYfiU"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "4. Let $\\widehat{X} = \\hat{X} = E[X|Y] = \\frac{1}{5}Y = 0.2 Y$. The residual etimation error is $Z = X - 0.2 Y$.\n",
        "* **Mean:** $E[Z] = E[X] - 0.2 E[Y] = 0 - 0 = 0$.\n",
        "\n",
        "  therefore E[z] is 0.\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Orthogonality:** $\\text{Cov}(Z, Y) = E[ZY] = E[(X - 0.2Y)Y] = E[XY] - 0.2 E[Y^2]$.\n",
        "    * $E[XY] = 1$ and $E[Y^2] = 5$.\n",
        "    * $\\text{Cov}(Z, Y) = 1 - 0.2(5) = 1 - 1 = 0$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Because $\\text{Cov}(Z,Y) = 0$, the remaining residual error contains zero linear correlation with our sensor data."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MFix9E1gbGse"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "5. Recall $h(\\mathscr{N}(\\mu, \\sigma^2)) = \\frac{1}{2}\\ln(2\\pi e \\sigma^2)$.\n",
        "\n",
        "* Diffrential entropy h(X): With $\\sigma_X^2 = 1$:\n",
        "$$h(X) = \\frac{1}{2}\\ln(2\\pi e) \\approx 1.4189 \\text{ nats}$$\n",
        "* Conditional  entropyh(X|Y): The conditional variance is\n",
        "$$\\sigma_{X|Y}^2 = \\sigma_X^2 - \\frac{\\text{Cov}(X,Y)^2}{\\text{Var}(Y)} = 1 - \\frac{1}{5} = 0.8.$$\n",
        "$$h(X|Y) = \\frac{1}{2}\\ln(2\\pi e \\cdot 0.8) \\approx 1.3073 \\text{ nats}$$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5LPdPuVvbM-i"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "6. $$I(X; Y) = h(X) - h(X|Y) = \\frac{1}{2}\\ln(1) - \\frac{1}{2}\\ln(0.8) = \\frac{1}{2}\\ln\\left(\\frac{1}{0.8}\\right) = \\frac{1}{2}\\ln(1.25) \\approx \\mathbf{0.1116 \\text{ nats}}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "percentage Uncertainty Removed:\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\frac{I(X;Y)}{h(X)} \\times 100\\% = \\frac{0.1116}{1.4189} \\times 100\\% \\approx \\mathbf{7.87\\%} $\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Mechanical noise is 100 instead of 4:\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\text{Var}(Y) = \\sigma_X^2 + \\sigma_Q^2 = 1 + 100 = 101$\n",
        "\n",
        "$\\sigma_{X|Y}^2 = 1 - \\frac{1^2}{101} = \\frac{100}{101}$\n",
        "\n",
        "the updated mutual infromation:\n",
        "$I(X;Y) = \\frac{1}{2}\\ln\\left(\\frac{\\sigma_X^2}{\\sigma_{X|Y}^2}\\right) = \\frac{1}{2}\\ln\\left(\\frac{1}{100/101}\\right) = \\frac{1}{2}\\ln\\left(\\frac{101}{100}\\right) \\approx \\mathbf{0.00497 \\text{ nats}}$\n",
        "\n",
        "new percentage of uncertainty removed:\n",
        "$\\frac{0.00497}{1.4189} \\times 100\\% \\approx \\mathbf{0.35\\%}$"
      ],
